Below is a **fully-detailed four-day plan for Week 1 of Term 1 (Tuesday 2 Sept – Friday 5 Sept)** in Grade 1 Early French Immersion.
The layout, depth, and notation match the Term 3 plans you liked:

* **Daily “why” statement** (direct link to a PEI Grade 1 outcome).
* **Timed schedule grid** with **Key moves & materials** and **Assessment / differentiation** for every block.
* **Prep & print list** (end of each day) keeps the workload transparent.

All content is aligned with the Government-of-PEI Grade 1 curricula for French Immersion Language Arts, Mathematics, Science, Health, and Arts ([princeedwardisland.ca][1], [princeedwardisland.ca][2], [princeedwardisland.ca][3]).

---

## Tuesday 2 September — “Bienvenue à la grande école!”

| Time                | Block                                                                             | Key moves & materials                                                                                                                        | Assessment & differentiation                                                  |
| ------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **8 :30 – 8 :45**   | **Accueil & Chant**                                                               | *Bonjour, comment ça va ?* call-and-response; feelings cards (🙂😟😡) on pocket chart.                                                       | Watch for students choosing the same card every day → flag for SEL follow-up. |
| **8 :45 – 9 :15**   | **FLA mini-lesson 1**<br>**Outcome (GCO 1):** express simple personal info.       | Introduce sound **/a/**⟶ mouth-mirror demo; chant “Aa comme avion”. Students trace “a” in air with two fingers.                              | Quick ✓: each student says */a/* plus a word; teacher records on roster.      |
| **9 :15 – 9 :35**   | **FLA mini-lesson 2**                                                             | Big-book **« À l’école »** (pattern *“Voici la… voici le…”*). Shared pointing, echo read two pages.                                          | Anecdotal note on one-to-one tracking skill.                                  |
| **9 :45 – 10 :30**  | **Mathematics**<br>**Outcome 1.N.1:** count to 10.                                | “Mystery Bag” ten-frame game: reveal counters (≤ 5) → students show same number on foam ten-frame.                                           | Exit slip: draw dots for the number teacher calls (0-5).                      |
| **10 :45 – 11 :30** | **Science – Five Senses launch**<br>**Outcome 205-1:** use senses to observe.     | Five carousel stations (sound tubes, scent jars, fabric swatches, kaleidoscope, salt/sugar taste sheet). French labels on each sense poster. | Clipboard “sens que j’utilise” pictograms—teacher checks at station change.   |
| **12 :45 – 1 :15**  | **Health – Class rules brainstorm**                                               | Read ppt of PEI safety expectations; students suggest 3 class rules, vote with sticky stars.                                                 | Photograph rule chart; later revisit for self-assessment.                     |
| **1 :15 – 2 :00**   | **Visual Arts – Self-portrait (line focus)**<br>**Outcome VA 1.1:** explore line. | Use handheld mirrors & black crayons → outline head, facial features; no colour yet.                                                         | Teacher note: pencil grip, spatial awareness.                                 |

**Prep / printing tonight**

* Feelings cards (laminate), “Aa comme avion” poster, five-senses pictogram sheet, sticky stars.

---

## Wednesday 3 September — “J’écoute, je touche”

| Time                | Block                              | Key moves & materials                                                                                               | Assessment & differentiation                                          |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **8 :30 – 8 :50**   | **Fluency warm-up**                | Re-sing “Bonjour” + “Aa-/a/ air-tracing” refresher; intro sound **/i/** (mirror demo).                              | Thumbs-up if they feel tongue is *up front* for /i/.                  |
| **8 :50 – 9 :30**   | **FLA – Shared reading**           | Revisit **« À l’école »** pp. 3-6; students echo full sentence, clap on \*/a/ & */i/* sounds.                       | Running note: who claps only after peers? plan modelling.             |
| **9 :40 – 10 :25**  | **Mathematics**                    | Outdoor “Leaf Tally”: each team collects 7 leaves, lines up & counts chorally 1-7-…-10. Record on mini whiteboards. | Partner coach for one-to-one errors; teacher snap photo evidence.     |
| **10 :40 – 11 :20** | **Science – Texture sort**         | Use yesterday’s fabrics + today’s leaves → Venn “doux et rugueux”. Vocabulary cards.                                | Tick inventory sheet; reteach if ≤ 3 correct items.                   |
| **12 :45 – 1 :05**  | **Health – Feelings colour wheel** | Mix red/yellow/blue tempera; associate feelings (rouge = colère, etc.).                                             | Students point wheel section that matches morning card; note changes. |
| **1 :05 – 1 :45**   | **Art – Colour wash**              | Water-down tempera over yesterday’s self-portrait; resist crayon lines pop.                                         | Peer “I notice bold lines” share.                                     |

**Tonight’s prep:**
Laminate Venn labels *doux* / *rugueux*, refill leaf bags, print feelings wheel halves.

---

## Thursday 4 September — “Nos règles, nos nombres”

| Time                | Block                                                                                 | Key moves & materials                                                                       | Assessment                                           |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| **8 :30 – 8 :50**   | **FLA warm-up**                                                                       | Name-word-wall: students stick magnetic name under first-letter header.                     | Photo wall for literacy record.                      |
| **8 :50 – 9 :25**   | **Dictée rapide (*/a / i/* VC words)**                                                | Words: *la, ma, mi, ici, ami*. Students use mini dry-erase boards.                          | Teacher checklist for letter formation.              |
| **9 :30 – 10 :10**  | **Mathematics – Comparing sets**                                                      | Use double-hula-hoop mats: drop bears into each hoop; students hold >,<,= paddles.          | Spot-check 3 sts per round; jot quick note.          |
| **10 :25 – 11 :05** | **Social Studies – Class rule charter**<br>**Outcome GCO B:** understand roles/rules. | Re-read brainstorm; in pairs draw one rule. Compile into big poster; all sign name.         | Video 30 s “rule tour” for families.                 |
| **12 :45 – 1 :20**  | **Health – Hand-washing demo**                                                        | Glitter-germ lotion, black-light box, six-step washing poster ([princeedwardisland.ca][2]). | Count residual sparkles; graph clean vs germy hands. |
| **1 :20 – 2 :00**   | **Art – Texture leaf rubbings**                                                       | Leaf under paper, crayon side-rub; mount on warm-coloured cardstock.                        | Gallery walk sticky “Wow!” note.                     |

*Print tonight:* paddle symbols > < =, “six steps” poster (11×17), parent email with rule-tour link.

---

## Friday 5 September — “Je peux lire déjà!”

| Time                | Block                                | Key moves & materials                                                                                              | Assessment                                               |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| **8 :30 – 9 :00**   | **FLA – Shared “Rules Rap”**         | Chant class rules (poster) with body percussion; highlight capital / period.                                       | Anecdotal: who keeps rhythm.                             |
| **9 :00 – 9 :30**   | **FLA – First independent reading**  | Book baskets: wordless Level A + *« À l’école »* copies; teach “3-finger read” (picture → first letter → re-read). | Confer with 4 focus students — note print-concept skill. |
| **9 :40 – 10 :30**  | **Math – Pattern bracelets**         | String beads in AB pattern (2 colours); extension ABC. Students record pattern on strip.                           | Pattern strip photo; identify core orally.               |
| **10 :45 – 11 :15** | **Science – Five-senses reflection** | Each table chooses 1 sense & creates freeze-drama; classmates guess en français.                                   | Checklist: vocabulary accuracy.                          |
| **12 :45 – 1 :15**  | **Health – Feelings wheel check-in** | Students move clip to wheel sector; discuss coping strategy if in yellow/red.                                      | Log wheel movements for SEL note.                        |
| **1 :15 – 2 :00**   | **Art – Finish self-portrait**       | Add wax-resist background shapes; mount with leaf rubbing border.                                                  | Exit ticket: “Je suis fier de \_\_\_ dans mon portrait.” |

Weekly wrap-up: send home photo collage of stations with brief parent note (English + French) linking to PEI curriculum strands ([princeedwardisland.ca][1]).

