Below are **fully-scaffolded, “ready-to-teach” day plans for Week 2 and Week 3 of Term 1 (Mon 8 Sept – Fri 19 Sept)**.
The layout, depth and notation match the Week 1 template you approved:

* **Daily “why” statement** ties each day to a *specific* PEI Grade 1 outcome.

  * French-Language Arts (FLA) outcomes = GCO 1-4 ([princeedwardisland.ca][1])
  * Mathematics outcomes = 1.N.1 – 1.N.4 ([princeedwardisland.ca][2])
  * Science outcomes (Five Senses / Materials) = SCO 205-1 etc. ([princeedwardisland.ca][3])
  * Social-Studies outcomes (Rules/Groups) taken from Grade 1 guide ([princeedwardisland.ca][4])
* **Timed schedule grids** – identical bell-times to Week 1.
* **Key moves & materials** + **Assessment / differentiation** in every block.
* **End-of-day “Prep & print” lists** keep workload clear.

