## WEEK 2 (Mon 8 Sept – Fri 12 Sept)

### Monday – “Les sons /e/ et /o/”

| Time        | Block                                                                                                                                                 | Key moves & materials                                                   | Assessment & differentiation |
| ----------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| 08:30-08:45 | **Accueil & Chant** – feelings check + “Éléphant / Oiseau” gesture-song.                                                                              | Observe students who still stick to one emotion card.                   |                              |
| 08:45-09:15 | **FLA Mini-lesson 1** (GCO 2) – mouth-mirror demo for **/e/**; chant “Éé éléphant”. Air-trace *é* on chart lines.                                     | ✓ Quick oral: each child offers a */e/* word; note substitution errors. |                              |
| 09:15-09:35 | **FLA Mini-lesson 2** – introduce **/o/** with “Ô ô orignal”. Shared “sound hunt” in classroom labels.                                                | Anecdotal list of two students who found ≥ 3 labels.                    |                              |
| 09:45-10:30 | **Math** (SCO 1.N.1) – build numbers **11-15** with popsicle bundles + singles; record on tens/ones T-chart.                                          | Exit slip: draw sticks for teacher-called 14.                           |                              |
| 10:45-11:30 | **Science** (SCO 205-1) – **Waterproof vs Absorbent** lab. Dropper bottles, felt, foil, wax paper, sponge. T-chart “absorbe / n’absorbe pas”.         | ✓ Sticker on chart for correct conclusion; reteach if misconception.    |                              |
| 12:45-13:15 | **Health / Art** – **Warm vs Cool scribble wash**. Students scribble wax lines warm (yellow/red) one half, cool (blue/green) other; paint light wash. | Peer “thumbs-up for colour family”.                                     |                              |
| 13:15-14:00 | **Art** – mount warm-cool piece; gallery walk “Je remarque…” sticky.                                                                                  | Photo for portfolio.                                                    |                              |

**Prep tonight:** print /e/ & /o/ sound cards, laminate “absorbe / non” headers, cut 60 popsicle bundles of 10.

---

### Tuesday – “Mots outils : le / la / un”

*Daily why*: build first three French sight-words to support one-to-one tracking (GCO 3).

| Time        | Block                                                                                                | Key moves & materials                                     | Assessment |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| 08:30-08:50 | Re-sing sound chants; pocket-chart sight-word **le / la / un** reveal.                               | Note who confuses *le* & *la* gender.                     |            |
| 08:50-09:25 | **Guided Reading A-level** (pattern *“Voici le \_\_\_”*). Highlight target word with highlight tape. | Anecdotal miscues; prompt cross-checking picture/letter.  |            |
| 09:30-10:10 | **Math** – copy & extend **AB/ABC** patterns with linking cubes → photograph on iPads.               | ✓ Teacher verifies core identification.                   |            |
| 10:25-11:05 | **Science** – sort 10 classroom items by use/material; label card in French (*bois, plastique*).     | Quick check: ≥ 3 correct per child.                       |            |
| 12:45-13:05 | **Health – Emotion charades**; teams act “content, triste, fâché”.                                   | Class guess with word-cards.                              |            |
| 13:05-13:45 | **Art – Emotion masks** (paper plates, elastic).                                                     | Observation of scissor grip; masks stored for SEL corner. |            |

Prep: Highlight tape on A-level books; print pattern task cards; prep plate-mask set.

