# WEEK 4 (Mon 22 Sept – Fri 26 Sept)

**Weekly FLA target**: master digraph **ou** and new high-frequency word *est* (GCO 2)
**Math target**: model & solve **addition ≤ 5** word problems (1.N.3)
**Science target**: investigate floating / sinking & reasons (SCO 100-11, 101-3)
**Social target**: practise classroom-rule citizenship (1.1.1)
**Arts target**: explore symmetry & warm-colour contrast (VA 1.1)

| **Time**      | **Mon 22** – *Digraph “ou” splash!*                                                                                                   | **Tue 23** – *Parts & wholes*                                                     | **Wed 24** – *Recyclable or trash?*                         | **Thu 25** – *Domino doubles*                                 | **Fri 26** – *Story-problem showcase*          |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| 08 :30-08 :45 | **Greeting/chant** – feelings + *ou* mouth-mirror demo; “OU-OU-hibou” echo.                                                           | Chant review; *est* word-wall flip & cheer.                                       | Warm-up → speed-round *ou* word hunt around room.           | Feelings cards; *est/ou* quick flash-quiz.                    | Rap recap of all *ou* words + *est*.           |
| 08 :45-09 :15 | **FLA 1** — air-trace *ou* letters; mini-booklet *« Où est la boule ? »*.                                                             | Shared read big-book pp. 3-5; highlight *est*.                                    | Guided reading *Décode 2* – check cueing system.            | Dictée (4 *ou* CV + 1 sentence *Il est…*).                    | Reader’s-theatre retell of booklet (pairs).    |
| 09 :15-09 :35 | **FLA 2** — pocket-chart scramble sentences using *est*. ✓ each child rebuilds one line.                                              | Word-wall toss: students throw beanbag, must say new *ou* word & sentence.        | Running-record slot #1 (others: rainbow-write ou/est).      | Running-record slot #2.                                       | Anecdotal rubric: expression & pacing.         |
| 09 :45-10 :30 | **Math** — read pictorial story “2 poissons + 3 poissons”; act out with counters; equation strip 2+3. Exit card: their own ≤ 5 story. | **Part-Part-Whole bars** ≤ 5; students place bears in cup halves then whole tray. | **Number-line hops** add 4, add 1. ✓ photo 3 sample boards. | **Domino doubles** station, doubles rap; build equation book. | **Addition quiz** 10 item mix ≤ 5.             |
| 10 :45-11 :30 | **Science** — Foil-boat build #1; predict coin cargo; test & record.                                                                  | Chart float/sink coin counts; debrief why foil floats.                            | Card-sort: recycle / landfill; glue to T-chart.             | Revise foil-boats; second test; compare data.                 | Reflection drawing “My best boat because…”.    |
